<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2855<hi rend="superscript">7/28</hi>: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T12:00:00-04:00">May 29,
                                    1940—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>147. For Kirk from the Under Secretary. Your 426, May 28, 2 p.m. The
                            Secretary and I both feel you should come immediately to the United
                            States on leave of absence. Try and make arrangements to come by clipper
                            if possible. We will announce here that your return is solely to take a
                            long postponed and much needed leave of absence in this country.
                            [Welles.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>